TITLE: Processing GitHub Webhook Events with FastAPI in Python
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines an async function to handle GitHub webhook events. It processes different event types, updates the database, and performs specific actions based on the event. The function uses FastAPI's Depends for dependency injection and interacts with various services and models.
SOURCE: https://github.com/polarsource/polar/blob/main/clients/apps/web/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Python
CODE:
```
async def process_github_webhook_event(
    event: GithubWebhookEvent,
    db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db),
    github_personal_access_token_service: GithubPersonalAccessTokenService = Depends(
        GithubPersonalAccessTokenService
    ),
    repository_service: RepositoryService = Depends(RepositoryService),
    organization_service: OrganizationService = Depends(OrganizationService),
    issue_service: IssueService = Depends(IssueService),
    pull_request_service: PullRequestService = Depends(PullRequestService),
    badge_service: BadgeService = Depends(BadgeService),
    pledge_service: PledgeService = Depends(PledgeService),
    user_service: UserService = Depends(UserService),
) -> None:
    # Process the event based on its type
    match event.event:
        case "issues":
            await process_issue_event(
                event,
                db,
                github_personal_access_token_service,
                repository_service,
                organization_service,
                issue_service,
                badge_service,
                pledge_service,
                user_service,
            )
        case "pull_request":
            await process_pull_request_event(
                event,
                db,
                github_personal_access_token_service,
                repository_service,
                organization_service,
                pull_request_service,
                badge_service,
                pledge_service,
                user_service,
            )
        case "repository":
            await process_repository_event(
                event,
                db,
                github_personal_access_token_service,
                repository_service,
                organization_service,
            )
        case "organization":
            await process_organization_event(
                event,
                db,
                github_personal_access_token_service,
                organization_service,
            )
        case "installation":
            await process_installation_event(
                event,
                db,
                github_personal_access_token_service,
                repository_service,
                organization_service,
            )
        case "installation_repositories":
            await process_installation_repositories_event(
                event,
                db,
                github_personal_access_token_service,
                repository_service,
                organization_service,
            )
        case _:
            logger.info(f"Unhandled event type: {event.event}")
```

